<title>USA: BEFORE THE BELL -Tobaccos rise, Clarify off.</title>
<headline>BEFORE THE BELL -Tobaccos rise, Clarify off.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tobacco stocks rose ahead of Wednesday's U.S. market open after a news report detailed secret talks that may lead to a settlement of cigarette litigation.</p>
<p>The report of negotiations between tobacco plaintiffs and Philip Morris Cos Inc and RJR Nabisco Holdings Corp appeared in today's edition of the Wall Street Journal.</p>
<p>In early third market trade, Philip Morris climbed to 41 from 39, while RJR was poised to rise with a 31-5/16 bid, up from 30-1/4, traders said.</p>
